Rails Action View: FormBuilder Concepts
=======================================
Rails provides form helpers to work with forms to set controls, naming and the attributes.
Rails Form Basic Structure:
	<%= form_with do |form| %>
		form controlls
	<% end %>

	it generates a html form with the value of method attributes set to post => methd: post
	and the value of attributes action set to current page => action: '/'
	<form action="/home" accept-charset="UTF-8" method="post">
	  <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="Lz6ILqUEs2CGdDa-oz38TqcqQORavGnbGkG0CQA8zc8peOps-K7sHgFSTPSkBx89pQxh3p5zPIkjoOTiA_UWbQ" autocomplete="off">
	  Form contents
	</form>

Form Helpers Different Methods:
-------------------------------
<%= form.checkbox :biography %>
<%= form.label :biography, "Biography" %>
<%= form.checkbox :romance %>
<%= form.label :romance, "Romance" %>
<%= form.checkbox :mystery %>
<%= form.label :mystery, "Mystery" %>
<%= form.date_field :born_on %>
<%= form.time_field :started_at %>
<%= form.datetime_local_field :graduation_day %>
<%= form.month_field :birthday_month %>
<%= form.week_field :birthday_week %>
<%= form.password_field :password %>
<%= form.email_field :address %>
<%= form.telephone_field :phone %>
<%= form.url_field :homepage %>




Working With Rails Form Helpers
-------------------------------
a. A Generic Search Form
	<%= form_with url: "/search", method: :get do |form| %>
	  <%= form.label :query, "Search for:" %>
	  <%= form.search_field :query %>
	  <%= form.submit "Search" %>
	<% end %>
	here lets demonstrate the attributes:
		form_with  			=> to set up the form helper object
		url: path  			=> to set the path it will go
		form.label 			=> to set the form label
		form.search_field	=> to set the search field
		form.submit 		=> to set the submit input field button where type="submit"
		:query 				=> under label :query refers to its attribute for="query"
		:query 				=> under form.search_field this :query refers to name ="query", id="query"


b. Form With Model Object
	<%= form_with model: @book do |form| %>
	  <div>
	    <%= form.label :title %>
	    <%= form.text_field :title %>
	  </div>
	  <div>
	    <%= form.label :author %>
	    <%= form.text_field :author %>
	  </div>
	  <%= form.submit %>
	<% end %>

	above generates the following html:
		<form action="/books" accept-charset="UTF-8" method="post">
		  <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="ChwHeyegcpAFDdBvXvDuvbfW7yCA3e8gvhyieai7DhG28C3akh-dyuv-IBittsjPrIjETlQQvQJ91T77QQ8xWA" autocomplete="off">
		  <div>
		    <label for="book_title">Title</label>
		    <input type="text" name="book[title]" id="book_title">
		  </div>
		  <div>
		    <label for="book_author">Author</label>
		    <input type="text" name="book[author]" id="book_author">
		  </div>
		  <input type="submit" name="commit" value="Create Book" data-disable-with="Create Book">
		</form>

c. Form With Method Object
	- Supported methods: form_with(url: search_path, method: "method_type")

	<%= form_with url: "/posts/1", method: :patch do |form| %>
	  <%= form.button "Delete", formmethod: :delete, data: { confirm: "Are you sure?" } %>
	  <%= form.button "Update" %>
	<% end %>

	it generates the following:
	<form accept-charset="UTF-8" action="/posts/1" method="post">
	  <input name="_method" type="hidden" value="patch" />
	  <input name="authenticity_token" type="hidden" value="f755bb0ed134b76c432144748a6d4b7a7ddf2b71" />
	  <!-- ... -->

	  <button type="submit" formmethod="post" name="_method" value="delete" data-confirm="Are you sure?">Delete</button>
	  <button type="submit" name="button">Update</button>
	</form>

d. Form Select Box Dropdown
	- Suppoted Format:
		1. <%= form.select :city, ["Berlin", "Chicago", "Madrid"] %>							# generates html dropdown having value and text as the given array
		2. <%= form.select :city, [["Berlin", "BE"], ["Chicago", "CHI"], ["Madrid", "MD"]] %>   # generates html dropdown having value ["BE", "CHI", "MD"] and text as ["Berlin", "Chicago", "Madrid"]

	See the html generated, for format -1, and 2
	<select name="city" id="city">
	  <option value="Berlin">Berlin</option>
	  <option value="Chicago">Chicago</option>
	  <option value="Madrid">Madrid</option>
	</select>

	<select name="city" id="city">
	  <option value="BE">Berlin</option>
	  <option value="CHI">Chicago</option>
	  <option value="MD">Madrid</option>
	</select>

	- Grouping Option Setup
		<%= form.select :city,
	      {
	        "Europe" => [ ["Berlin", "BE"], ["Madrid", "MD"] ],
	        "North America" => [ ["Chicago", "CHI"] ],
	      },
	      selected: "CHI" %>
	which generates the following:
		<select name="city" id="city">
		  <optgroup label="Europe">
		    <option value="BE">Berlin</option>
		    <option value="MD">Madrid</option>
		  </optgroup>
		  <optgroup label="North America">
		    <option value="CHI" selected="selected">Chicago</option>
		  </optgroup>
		</select>

	- binding with model object
		@person = Person.new(city: "MD")
		<%= form_with model: @person do |form| %>
		  <%= form.select :city, [["Berlin", "BE"], ["Chicago", "CHI"], ["Madrid", "MD"]] %>
		<% end %>
		<select name="person[city]" id="person_city">
		  <option value="BE">Berlin</option>
		  <option value="CHI">Chicago</option>
		  <option value="MD" selected="selected">Madrid</option>
		</select>
e. Form With File Upload: file_field Helper
	- see the first example without specifiying the enctype, form helpers- file_field automatically adds that
	 but if wanted can also manually set that see the second example which manually adds it.
	- form with enctype="multipart/form-data" attribute
		<%= form_with model: @person do |form| %>
		  <%= form.file_field :csv_file %>
		<% end %>
		or,
		<%= form_with url: "/uploads", multipart: true do |form| %>
		  <%= file_field_tag :csv_file %>
		<% end %>

		which generates the following:
		<form enctype="multipart/form-data" action="/people" accept-charset="UTF-8" method="post">
			<!-- ... -->
		</form>
















